quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  16,51,"For God hath said, \"Take not to yourselves two gods, for He is one God: me, therefore! yea, me revere"
  16,52,All in the Heavens and in the Earth is His! His due unceasing service! Will ye then fear any other than God
  16,53,"And all your blessings are assuredly from God: then, when trouble befalleth you, to Him ye turn for help"
  16,54,"Then when He relieveth you of the trouble, lo! some of you join associates with your Lord"
  16,55,"To prove how thankless are they for our gifts! Enjoy yourselves then: but in the end ye shall know the truth"
  16,56,"And for idols, of which they know nothing, they set apart a share of our bounties! By God ye shall be called to account for your devices"
  16,57,And they ascribe daughters unto God! Glory be to Him! But they desire them not for themselves
  16,58,"For when the birth of a daughter is announced to any one of them, dark shadows settle on his face, and he is sad"
  16,59,"He hideth him from the people because of the ill tidings: shall he keep it with disgrace or bury it in the dust? Are not their judgments wrong"
  16,60,"To whatever is evil may they be likened who believe not in a future life; but God is to be likened to whatever is loftiest: for He is the Mighty, the Wise"